These bands alternate pear and round diamonds in a repeating pattern — the pear diamonds set east-west, the round diamonds set in standard prong mounts. They create a visual rhythm that is more complex than a single-shape eternity band and pair especially well alongside pear solitaires because the band echoes the center stone's shape without matching it exactly.

